This page documents the Cognito Worker Service architecture, message contract, deployment model, runtime behavior, monitoring setup, and current production considerations.

At a glance

Runtime: Go worker running on Kubernetes

Input queue: cognito-request

Output queue: cognito-response

Primary dependency: AWS Cognito

Metrics endpoint: /metrics on port 2112

Transport: RabbitMQ over amqps:// for production

AWS access model

The worker uses one dedicated IAM user for AWS authentication.

IAM username: cognito_user

The Kubernetes Secret stores the access key and secret key for cognito_user as AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY.

The IAM user must have a proper least-privilege policy that allows only the required AWS Cognito operations.

