Overview
The Cognito Worker Service is a Go-based, event-driven microservice that automates Cognito provisioning and user lifecycle operations in an asynchronous workflow. It sits between producer systems and downstream consumers, taking requests from RabbitMQ, executing Cognito actions in AWS, and publishing result messages back to RabbitMQ.

This design helps decouple provisioning requests from execution, improves resilience during transient failures, and provides operational visibility through Prometheus-compatible metrics.

Purpose and responsibilities
The service acts as a backend worker for Cognito-related automation.

Consumes provisioning and user-management requests from cognito-request

Executes Cognito setup and user operations in AWS

Publishes processing outcomes to cognito-response

Applies OAuth callback, logout, and redirect configuration dynamically

Exposes runtime metrics for monitoring and alerting

