Hosted UI
The Cognito Hosted UI login endpoint follows this pattern:

https://<domain>.auth.<region>.amazoncognito.com/login

The Cognito Hosted UI forgot password endpoint follows this pattern:

https://<domain>.auth.<region>.amazoncognito.com/forgotPassword?client_id=<app-client-id>&response_type=code&scope=openid+email+profile&redirect_uri=<callback-url>

If the application uses its own custom login page instead of the Cognito Hosted UI login page, the forgot password page should be handled by the application frontend using the same query-parameter pattern. The recommended custom forgot password URL pattern is:

https://<your-app-domain>/forgot-password?client_id=<app-client-id>&response_type=code&scope=openid+email+profile&redirect_uri=https://<your-app-domain>/callback

The custom forgot password page should collect the user email or username and call Cognito forgot password/reset password APIs, while using the configured callback or application route for the final redirect after reset.

Admin user behavior
Email is marked as verified

The code sets the admin user password permanently during creation. After that, the admin user can reset the password later by using the Cognito forgot password/reset password flow.

Admin-user creation is retry-enabled

