Batch user creation event
Use USER_CREATE to create multiple Cognito users in one request. Producer systems send a JSON message with env and companyCode; the worker maps these values to the correct Cognito user pool. 



{
  "action": "USER_CREATE",
  "env": "dev",
  "companyCode": "acme",
  "users": [
    {
      "username": "user1",
      "email": "user1@acme.com"
    },
    {
      "username": "user2",
      "email": "user2@acme.com"
    }
  ]
}
Field

Purpose

action

Must be USER_CREATE for batch user creation

env

Identifies the target environment and is used with companyCode to resolve the Cognito user pool

companyCode

Business or tenant identifier used with env to resolve the Cognito user pool

users

Array of users to create in batch

username

Username for the Cognito user

email

Email address assigned to the user. This field is required for user communication and for the Cognito forgot password/reset password flow after the code has set the user's password permanently.

User access disable event
Use USER_DISABLE to disable access for one or more existing Cognito users without deleting the accounts. The payload does not require userPoolId; the worker resolves the target user pool from env and companyCode.



{
  "action": "USER_DISABLE",
  "env": "dev",
  "companyCode": "acme",
  "usernames": [
    "user1",
    "user2"
  ]
}
Field

Purpose

action

Must be USER_DISABLE for access disable requests

env

Identifies the target environment and is used with companyCode to resolve the Cognito user pool

companyCode

