Lifecycle operation note

USER_DISABLE is reversible because the Cognito user remains in the user pool. USER_DELETE is destructive and should be used only when permanent account removal is intended.

Environment configuration
The service depends on environment variables for AWS connectivity, queue names, and RabbitMQ access.



AWS_REGION=us-east-1
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<access-key-for-cognito_user>
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<secret-key-for-cognito_user>
RABBITMQ_URL=amqps://user:password@host:5671/KCP_Dev_vhost
RABBITMQ_REQUEST_QUEUE=cognito-request
RABBITMQ_RESPONSE_QUEUE=cognito-response
Required broker and AWS access settings

TLS must be enabled for production use, valid RabbitMQ credentials must be supplied, and the RabbitMQ virtual host must be present in the connection URL, for example KCP_Dev_vhost.

AWS credentials must belong to IAM user cognito_user. This user should have a proper least-privilege IAM policy for the required Cognito operations only.

