FAQ

Why does the service use manual ACK?
Manual acknowledgment ensures a message is confirmed only after processing completes successfully. This helps avoid losing work during transient failures.


What queue names are used by default?
The default inbound queue is cognito-request and the default outbound queue is cognito-response.


How does the worker authenticate to AWS?
The worker authenticates to AWS using one dedicated IAM user named cognito_user. The access key and secret key for this IAM user are stored in the Kubernetes Secret as AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY. The user must have a proper least-privilege policy for the required Cognito operations.


What endpoint is used for monitoring?
The service exposes Prometheus-compatible metrics at /metrics on port 2112.


How is the default redirect selected if it is not provided?
The fallback behavior sets the default redirect to the first value in callbackUrls.
